- 'attending doctors' refers to healthcare providers with the role 'doctor'.

- "visits" refers to the number of encounters a patient has had with the medical facility;
- "diagnosed with at least one condition" means the patient has at least one recorded diagnosis;
- "medical journey" is a metaphorical term for the patient's history of medical encounters and diagnoses.

